===Municipalities=== Tuscany is also divided in 287 ''[[Comune|comuni]]'' ([[municipality|municipalities]]), which have even more history, having been established in the [[Middle Ages]] when they were the main places of government. 18 ''comuni'' (10 provincial capitals) have more than 45,000 inhabitants, a large majority of which are ruled by the centre-left.
